page.title: 05H.M.S. Warrior in Hartlepool
page.content: {10. What was she doing before she {came to Hartlepool?} In 1927 she was fitted as a pontoon atached to an oil fuel depot and in 1929 she was moved to Pembroke Dock to serve that purpose until 1979. {11. How long has it been in {Hartlepool?} The Warrior has been in Hartlepool 5 years, she came in September 1979 and she has been in the Coal Dock ever since. {12. Why is it here?} The Warrior is here to undergo repairs and at the end of June 1985 there was a small fire on board which will delay repairs. {13. Where is the H.M.S. Warrior?} The H.M.S. Warrior is in old Hartlepool at the Coal Dock which was used for bringing in coal.
